                    "id": "deforestation_response",
                    "description": "Deforestation forcing — 2 Pg C/yr (Fd = 2.0e12/31557600 kg/s) sustained for 50 model years (1.57788e9 s), with no fossil fuel or reforestation forcing. Deforestation transfers carbon from terrestrial biota to the atmosphere: biota M5 declines below its 5.80e14 kg preindustrial value, soils/detritus M6 declines (less litterfall input), and atmospheric M1 rises. The land-use scaling factor G falls to 1 − a_d·Fd·t/M5_0 = 1 − 0.23·(2 Pg C/yr·50 yr)/(580 Pg C) = 0.96034 — the closed-form integral of the constant-forcing D(G) equation. M7 is untouched (Ff=0). Pins all 11 variables at 50 yr.",
