                {
                    "id": "reforestation_response",
                    "description": "Reforestation forcing — 2 Pg C/yr (Fr = 2.0e12/31557600 kg/s) sustained for 50 model years (1.57788e9 s), with no fossil fuel or deforestation forcing. Reforestation transfers carbon from the atmosphere to terrestrial biota: biota M5 grows above its 5.80e14 kg preindustrial value, soils/detritus M6 grows, and atmospheric M1 is drawn down. The land-use scaling factor G rises to 1 + a_r·Fr·t/M5_0 = 1 + 1.0·(2 Pg C/yr·50 yr)/(580 Pg C) = 1.17241. The ocean outgassing fluxes F21/F31 fall as the depleted atmosphere lets the oceans release less CO2. Pins all 11 variables at 50 yr.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"Fr": 63376.1756280579},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1577880000.0},
